-- Chelsea Considers Bidding for Villa’s Benteke: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-07-09T08:05:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-09/chelsea-considers-bidding-for-villa-s-benteke-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers with clickable Internet links.  Chelsea Considers Benteke  Chelsea is considering a move for Aston Villa striker
Christian Benteke after the Belgian international handed in a
transfer request, the  Daily Telegraph reported .  Villa owner  Randy Lerner  will demand a fee of at least 25
million pounds ($37.5 million) for Benteke, who has three years
remaining on his contract, the newspaper added.  Suarez Lined Up  Chelsea manager  Jose Mourinho  is lining up a 40 million-pound offer for Liverpool striker  Luis Suarez , the  Daily Mirror
reported .  Arsenal already had a bid rejected for the Uruguayan
forward, who has a clause in his contract stating that Liverpool
must listen to offers of at least 40 million pounds, the
newspaper added.  Suarez has told Liverpool that he wants to leave the Reds
to play in the Champions League, the  Sun reported .  Bigger Baines Bid  Manchester United  will return with an improved offer for
Everton defender  Leighton Baines , the  Daily Express reported .  Everton rejected a bid of about 10 million pounds 12 days
ago and United will increase its offer by about 3 million
pounds, the newspaper reported.  Fiorentina Forward  Manchester City is increasing its efforts to sign
Fiorentina’s Stevan Jovetic, who has a 27 million-pound buy-out
clause in his contract, the  Sun reported .  Liverpool, Chelsea and Arsenal are also interested in the
23-year-old forward, who has made it clear he wants to leave the
Italian club, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
